The South African weather service issued a warning today to inform the public to expect extreme heat on 12 January 2019. The maximum temperature is expected to reach 41°C and humidity levels are also expected to reach up to 90%. Extreme thunderstorms are expected in the late afternoon until approximately 21:00. Watch:11/01/2019 13h00 TO:11/01/2019 21h00 Severe Thunderstorms- are expected over the north-eastern parts of Mpumalanga (Ehlanzeni and northern and eastern parts of Nkangala Districts) from the afternoon today (Friday). — SA Weather Service (@SAWeatherServic) January 11, 2019   